This programm was created by Hagen Fritsch and updates by Sylvain Clayer under licence GPL

This programm is designed to make changing keycodes for DVB-T Remotes easier.
Works by patching the appropriate kernel-modules.

---------------------------------------------------

Needs to be run as root for patching kernel-modules.

Programm is designed for an azerty keyboard

---------------------------------------------------
Use:

1. Download the files named « dvb-remote-key-editor.py » and « input.h » in a same directory.

2. Launch a CLI (command line interface) and enter « $ gksudo python dvb-remote-key-editor.py ».

3. Choose the DVB-T Remote you want by clicking on the buttons or by the menu « Load ».

4. Make the changes you want in the keycodes.

5. Click on « Save changes to kernel module ».

6. Close the programm and write in a CLI to reload the kernel module:
    $ sudo rmmod name_of_the_kernel_module #(ex: dvb_usb_cinergyT2)
    $ sudo modprobe name_of_the_kernel_module #(ex: dvb_usb_cinergyT2)

Enjoy the remote...
